The paper deals with a geometric optimization problem involving rectangles in the 2D-plane, which suggests that it belongs to the computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. The use of dynamic programming and approximation algorithms also suggests that it could belong to the data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the mention of the weighted planar graph separator theorem suggests that it could also belong to the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category.
